definition.value: An oxo dicarboxylic acid that is adipic acid substituted by an oxo group at position 2.
A bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3alpha,7alpha,12beta-trihydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A glycosylmannose consisting of an alpha-D-galactopyranose residue and a beta-D-mannopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A straight-chain, sixteen-carbon, saturated long-chain fatty acid.
